if you can fill it up.

03:54.364 --> 03:56.758
Just get up there and have fun.
You'll be fine.

03:56.758 --> 03:58.847
How do you like
to be introduced?

03:58.847 --> 04:00.718
My name is fine.

04:00.718 --> 04:02.981
I like that. I like that.
That's old school.

04:02.981 --> 04:04.940
Just your name.
Like I said, bro,

04:04.940 --> 04:07.377
just have fun with it.

04:07.377 --> 04:11.512
Ladies and gentlemen,
please give a very warm welcome

04:11.512 --> 04:14.079
to a brand new face
in local comedy,

04:14.079 --> 04:16.212
Mr. Denny Briggs,
everybody!

04:16.212 --> 04:17.474
Denny Briggs!

04:17.474 --> 04:19.346
[AUDIENCE CLAPPING
AND CHEERING]

04:31.183 --> 04:32.272
[INHALES SHARPLY]

04:34.143 --> 04:37.538
I swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth,

04:37.538 --> 04:40.454
and nothing but the truth,
so help me God.

04:42.673 --> 04:46.677
The truth is, I'm gonna die
up here tonight.

04:46.677 --> 04:48.375
[SCATTERED LAUGHS]

04:48.375 --> 04:53.380
Now, the truth is
the funniest thing in comedy.

04:53.380 --> 04:55.512
It's what we can
all relate to,

04:55.512 --> 04:58.733
our work,
our relationships,

04:58.733 --> 05:01.431
love, lust, jealousy, hate,

05:01.431 --> 05:02.476
family.

05:04.608 --> 05:08.525
It's these truths
that make comedy funny.

05:08.525 --> 05:10.266
