I'm on trial...

05:10.266 --> 05:11.354
[AUDIENCE LAUGHS]

05:11.354 --> 05:15.053
...and you,
you are my jury.

05:15.053 --> 05:18.318
[AUDIENCE LAUGHS]

05:18.318 --> 05:20.058
Now, if you laugh
at the things that I say,

05:20.058 --> 05:21.973
well, it means
that I'm telling the truth,

05:21.973 --> 05:24.846
and the harder that you laugh,
the guiltier I become.

05:24.846 --> 05:26.935
[AUDIENCE LAUGHS]

05:26.935 --> 05:30.242
You see, I'm on trial
for murder.

05:30.242 --> 05:31.809
[AUDIENCE LAUGHS]

05:31.809 --> 05:34.029
And if found guilty
of this crime,

05:34.029 --> 05:37.989
I will take a gun,
put it against my temple,

05:37.989 --> 05:40.862
pull the trigger,
and blow my brains out.

05:40.862 --> 05:45.823
[AUDIENCE LAUGHS
AND APPLAUDS]

05:45.823 --> 05:47.259
I recently lost my job.

05:47.259 --> 05:49.131
