18:26.409 --> 18:27.454
Hey.

18:27.454 --> 18:28.803
Hey, Mads.

18:28.803 --> 18:31.066
Got any good jokes for me?

18:31.066 --> 18:32.415
Um...

18:34.896 --> 18:35.984
No.

18:35.984 --> 18:38.856
No, I... You?

18:38.856 --> 18:40.641
Cheeseburger
walks into a bar.

18:40.641 --> 18:42.730
Bartender says,
"Hey, buddy!

18:42.730 --> 18:44.079
We don't
serve food in here."

18:44.079 --> 18:45.385
[CHUCKLES]

18:45.385 --> 18:47.038
It's good to see you.

18:47.038 --> 18:48.257
It's good to see you.

18:48.257 --> 18:49.780
Where were you last week?

18:51.042 --> 18:52.043
Something came up.

18:52.043 --> 18:54.176
What came up?

18:54.176 --> 18:55.786
Actually,
I had to find a new job.

18:55.786 --> 18:57.658
[SIGHS]

18:57.658 --> 18:59.094
Funny, I forgot the part

18:59.094 --> 19:01.357
where you mentioned
you were looking.

19:01.357 --> 19:02.924
I thought you liked
the warehouse.

19:02.924 --> 19:04.621
I just thought it was time
for a change,

19:04.621 --> 19:07.668
so I'm gonna be a waiter
in a restaurant.

19:07.668 --> 19:09.148
Really?

19:09.148 --> 19:10.366
I heard they
have those there.

19:10.366 --> 19:11.280
Yeah.

19:11.280 --> 19:12.890
What restaurant?

19:12.890 --> 19:14.022
It's a little place.

19:14.022 --> 19:15.980
You wouldn't know it.

19:15.980 --> 19:18.766
I would have said something.
I-I would have told you sooner,

19:18.766 --> 19:20.985
just, it all happened
really quick.

19:20.985 --> 19:22.509
Well, I have some news,

19:22.509 --> 19:25.251
I mean, that is
if you're even interested.

19:25.251 --> 19:26.208
Of course.

19:28.341 --> 19:30.865
We're gonna be a family again,
after all these years.

19:30.865 --> 19:32.562
[♪♪♪]

19:32.562 --> 19:34.303
What do you mean?

19:34.303 --> 19:36.262
I mean,
brother and sister...

19:36.262 --> 19:37.567
a real family.

19:37.567 --> 19:39.265
We are a real family.

19:42.093 --> 19:43.530
Not like other families,
we're not.

19:45.053 --> 19:46.141
Not like this.

19:49.797 --> 19:51.190
You know I love you,
right, Denny?

19:51.190 --> 19:53.583
Of course.

19:53.583 --> 19:56.369
And you love me just the same
as you always have, right?

19:56.369 --> 19:59.067
Madison, what is it?
You're starting to scare me.

19:59.067 --> 20:01.287
I got parole.

20:03.289 --> 20:06.509
I'm getting released
at the end of the month.

20:06.509 --> 20:08.859
I-I'm gonna be on probation,

20:08.859 --> 20:11.558
but I'll be allowed to work
a-and travel some.

20:13.690 --> 20:14.952
Denny,
say something, please.

20:16.389 --> 20:18.304
Sorry, I just--
I wasn't prepared.

20:18.304 --> 20:19.522
It's okay.

20:21.089 --> 20:23.178
It's gonna be all right,
you know?

20:23.178 --> 20:25.049
Just like when we were kids.

20:25.049 --> 20:26.486
I'll make it
better this time.

20:32.927 --> 20:35.234
[GLASS CLATTERS]
Whoa, hey. Shaun.

20:35.234 --> 20:36.147
Hey.

20:42.719 --> 20:43.764
Denny!

20:43.764 --> 20:45.026
Hi.

20:45.026 --> 20:46.288
Hi, let me take
a look at you.

20:46.288 --> 20:47.724
[STAMMERS]
I'm sorry.

20:47.724 --> 20:49.378
Oh, no, it doesn't have
to be perfect,

20:49.378 --> 20:50.727
just presentable.
Okay.

20:50.727 --> 20:52.033
Okay?
I'm going to have you

20:52.033 --> 20:54.209
cover all two tops
and help with takeouts.

20:54.209 --> 20:56.255
Uh, have you met Shaun?

20:56.255 --> 20:59.040
And Sarah,
and that's Mandel.

20:59.040 --> 21:01.869
Sarah preps, does short order,
and answers takeouts.

21:01.869 --> 21:06.221
Mandel is our amazing
and talented chef.

21:06.221 --> 21:08.441
And Shaun,
can't forget Shaun,

21:08.441 --> 21:11.400
[CHUCKLES]
he cleans, does the dishes,
and closes the kitchen.

21:11.400 --> 21:12.401
Um, what else?

21:12.401 --> 21:13.750
Oh, your passcode

21:13.750 --> 21:15.709
for the register
is "sticky."

21:15.709 --> 21:17.841
That's S-T-I-C-K-Y.

21:17.841 --> 21:19.756
And tonight I'm going
to have you do inventory,

21:19.756 --> 21:21.802
so I can close the books
on Friday.

21:21.802 --> 21:23.238
Okay.
Okay?

21:23.238 --> 21:26.154
Okay.
Go ahead, get going.

21:26.154 --> 21:28.287
Oh, hold on.

21:28.287 --> 21:30.071
God forbid you forget these.

21:30.071 --> 21:31.638
Okay.

21:31.638 --> 21:33.335
Oh.

21:33.335 --> 21:35.250
Sorry.

21:35.250 --> 21:37.252
[SOFT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING]

21:44.825 --> 21:46.130
Denny.

21:46.130 --> 21:47.567
Hey.
Hey.

21:47.567 --> 21:49.133
You're gonna be great.

21:49.133 --> 21:51.048
Just remember,
treat 'em like our family.

21:51.048 --> 21:53.181
Okay. Yep.
Okay.

21:53.181 --> 21:54.791
[CHUCKLES]

22:04.758 --> 22:06.063
Hello.

22:06.063 --> 22:07.500
ALL: Hello.
How's everyone doing?

22:07.500 --> 22:08.675
We're starving.

22:08.675 --> 22:10.546
Me too.
I didn't eat breakfast.

22:10.546 --> 22:11.678
That's never
a good idea.

22:11.678 --> 22:12.809
Breakfast is the most

22:12.809 --> 22:14.028
important meal
of the day.

22:14.028 --> 22:15.377
I think so too.

22:15.377 --> 22:16.813
I'm sorry, could we get

22:16.813 --> 22:18.337
some drinks and the menus?

22:18.337 --> 22:21.122
Well, sir you want,
uh, you-- Waters?

22:21.122 --> 22:22.776
Waters are good.
Waters'll be fine.

22:22.776 --> 22:24.343
Waters, great.

22:24.343 --> 22:26.519
So you taking
the day off today?

22:26.519 --> 22:27.824
Excuse me?

22:27.824 --> 22:30.044
It was Monday,
and I thought maybe

22:30.044 --> 22:32.046
you were taking time off
to spend with the family.

22:32.046 --> 22:33.787
[SIGHS]
I think that's really great.

22:33.787 --> 22:35.310
Dad lost his job.

22:35.310 --> 22:37.312
Sweetheart, don't say that
about your father!

22:37.312 --> 22:38.531
Well, he did.
Oh, I didn't--

22:38.531 --> 22:40.184
I didn't lose it.

22:40.184 --> 22:43.405
I'm just taking
a little time off.

22:43.405 --> 22:45.842
[SIGHS]
You know, I lost my last job,

22:45.842 --> 22:48.628
and I thought I'd take
some time off too,

22:48.628 --> 22:49.716
but then, it was--

22:49.716 --> 22:51.152
Gotta get back to work--
I didn't

22:51.152 --> 22:53.197
lose my job.

22:53.197 --> 22:56.070
Could we please
just get the menus

22:56.070 --> 22:58.115
and order
some goddamn food!

22:58.115 --> 23:00.553
Dad, you're embarrassing us!
Sweetheart.

23:00.553 --> 23:01.467
This is ridiculous.

23:01.467 --> 23:02.555
I don't need to be

23:02.555 --> 23:03.947
interrogated
by some waiter!

23:03.947 --> 23:05.471
Hi, folks!

23:05.471 --> 23:06.820
What seems to be
the problem?

23:06.820 --> 23:08.212
His waiting style,

23:08.212 --> 23:09.562
it is not very appropriate.

23:09.562 --> 23:10.911
I'm sorry,
it's his first day.

23:10.911 --> 23:13.740
Then maybe you should
first teach him

23:13.740 --> 23:15.481
some good old
family manners.

23:15.481 --> 23:17.091
Absolutely.
We'll talk.

23:17.091 --> 23:18.788
Hey!
How 'bout this,

23:18.788 --> 23:21.312
first off, you've got
the complimentary sticky buns,

23:21.312 --> 23:23.227
I'd love to bring out
a cup of delicious

23:23.227 --> 23:25.795
homemade tomato rice soup, on
the house? How does that sound?

23:25.795 --> 23:27.231
All right.
Beverages coming up!

23:27.231 --> 23:28.537
Okay.

23:31.322 --> 23:33.760
You can only order something
that's six dollars or less.

23:35.631 --> 23:36.980
I was--

23:36.980 --> 23:38.939
Don't beat yourself up.

23:38.939 --> 23:41.376
[STUTTERS]
You said family, and I was,
I was trying to--

23:41.376 --> 23:43.465
You're doing great. Look...

23:43.465 --> 23:45.554
even in a family,
sometimes people are touchy,

23:45.554 --> 23:48.470
and, uh, it happens.
Don't worry about it.

23:48.470 --> 23:49.558
Back on the bicycle.

23:49.558 --> 23:50.733
Okay?
Okay.

23:50.733 --> 23:51.908
Four cups tomato rice soup,

23:51.908 --> 23:53.344
we're gonna comp them.

23:53.344 --> 23:54.781
Should I get the waters?
First?

23:54.781 --> 23:57.566
Get the waters first,
good thinking,

23:57.566 --> 23:59.046
uh, and some lemon,

23:59.046 --> 24:00.917
and maybe a little more ice
in the pitcher.

24:00.917 --> 24:02.353
Okay.

24:02.353 --> 24:03.703
Doing great, Denny.

24:06.401 --> 24:07.402
Back in the kitchen.

24:07.402 --> 24:08.229
Okay.
Yeah.

24:09.926 --> 24:12.102
[♪♪♪]

24:23.723 --> 24:25.028
Come on guys,
we need to get going!

24:27.074 --> 24:28.162
You know what?

24:28.162 --> 24:30.120
Why don't you do the honors?

24:30.120 --> 24:31.034
Okay.

24:33.210 --> 24:34.255
All right, Monday,

24:34.255 --> 24:35.474
what do we got?

24:35.474 --> 24:37.476
I vote
Mandel's meatloaf

24:37.476 --> 24:38.912
and mashed potato Monday.

24:38.912 --> 24:40.653
LLOYD: Too spicy.
MANDEL: I can cut down

24:40.653 --> 24:42.002
on the jalapenos.

24:42.002 --> 24:43.743
Come on, all in favor?

24:43.743 --> 24:45.658
Yeah!
All right.

24:45.658 --> 24:49.096
How about, uh,
chicken pot pie Tuesday?

24:49.096 --> 24:50.489
ALL:
Ah.

24:50.489 --> 24:52.665
I'm gonna put you
to work in the kitchen.

24:52.665 --> 24:54.405
Yeah, how long has he
been here now?

24:54.405 --> 24:56.495
Uh, I don't know, what,
like three weeks?

24:56.495 --> 24:57.713
SHAUN & MANDEL:
Three weeks!

24:57.713 --> 24:59.236
Ha, ha! Come on!

24:59.236 --> 25:00.542
You guys know
what that means?

25:00.542 --> 25:01.848
MANDEL: I sure do.
Don't you go

25:01.848 --> 25:03.502
scaring him away just yet.

25:03.502 --> 25:04.503
What?

25:04.503 --> 25:05.591
Oh, you don't--

25:05.591 --> 25:06.809
You don't really wanna know.

25:06.809 --> 25:08.158
No, I do. I wanna know.

25:08.158 --> 25:10.726
Well, it's
a Miller family tradition

25:10.726 --> 25:12.946
to take the newest member
of our family

25:12.946 --> 25:14.295
out on the town
for some fun

25:14.295 --> 25:15.557
and spirits.
Mm-hm.

25:15.557 --> 25:17.907
That is not
a family tradition.

25:17.907 --> 25:20.214
No, in fact,
it's more of an excuse

25:20.214 --> 25:22.695
for Mandel and Shaun
to get piss-ass drunk.

25:22.695 --> 25:25.175
You know what?
You can call it what you will,

25:25.175 --> 25:28.744
the fact remains, we all still
have to go out and formally,

25:28.744 --> 25:31.399
you know, welcome Denny
to the family. Ha-ha-ha!

25:31.399 --> 25:34.576
I mean,
I don't really drink much.

25:34.576 --> 25:36.317
MANDEL:
That's okay. We do.

25:36.317 --> 25:37.797
I do not want everyone
showin' up

25:37.797 --> 25:39.450
with a hangover tomorrow.

25:39.450 --> 25:41.191
SHAUN & MANDEL:
Yes, Grandpa Miller.

25:41.191 --> 25:42.541
I do have
tomorrow off, though.

25:42.541 --> 25:44.586
Ooh.
You should not have said that.

25:44.586 --> 25:46.675
Come on,
what do you guys say?

25:46.675 --> 25:48.372
Linda...

25:48.372 --> 25:49.809
Mm...
Oh, no.

25:49.809 --> 25:51.158
Sarah?

25:51.158 --> 25:53.073
Come on!
Mm, okay, okay, come on, Linda,

25:53.073 --> 25:54.422
we'll just have a couple.

25:54.422 --> 25:56.903
Famous last words.
Ha-ha-ha.

25:56.903 --> 25:58.774
Come on, Lloyd, wanna get
a drink tonight?

25:58.774 --> 26:00.515
LLOYD:
No. You go ahead.

26:00.515 --> 26:02.386
I am trusting you
to get these kids home

26:02.386 --> 26:03.866
at a reasonable hour.

26:03.866 --> 26:05.912
Grandpa knows best.
He does, he does.

26:05.912 --> 26:08.392
LLOYD:
I'm as young today
as the day I opened this joint.

26:08.392 --> 26:10.177
It's your wisdom we admire.
LLOYD: Yeah,

26:10.177 --> 26:11.961
well wise up to this then,
before you go,

26:11.961 --> 26:14.181
one of you wisenheimers
has to hightail it in

26:14.181 --> 26:16.575
to the women's bathroom.
The toilet's clogged up again.

26:17.837 --> 26:19.142
Come on.
Yes!

26:19.142 --> 26:20.883
[LINDA, LLOYD,
& MANDEL LAUGH]

26:20.883 --> 26:22.581
You always win!
Bye-bye!

26:24.321 --> 26:25.540
Okay, Wednesdays.

26:25.540 --> 26:26.846
LLOYD:
All right, Wednesdays.

26:26.846 --> 26:28.369
Wisenheimer pie?

26:28.369 --> 26:30.371
ALL:
Wisenheimer pie.

26:30.371 --> 26:32.025
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

26:32.025 --> 26:34.027
SARAH:
♪ Get drunk ♪

26:34.027 --> 26:35.071
Hey, guys.

26:35.071 --> 26:36.507
MANDEL:
Oh, my God. Hello!

26:36.507 --> 26:38.248
How are ya?

26:38.248 --> 26:39.554
SARAH: Good.
Hi, ladies.

26:39.554 --> 26:40.511
Hello.

26:40.511 --> 26:43.036
[CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

26:43.036 --> 26:46.039
MANDEL:
Ooh-hoo-hoo!

26:46.039 --> 26:48.998
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!

26:48.998 --> 26:50.217
[ALL LAUGH]

26:50.217 --> 26:52.088
Oh, wait, we need
to make a toast!

26:52.088 --> 26:54.047
Excuse me?
Yeah?

26:54.047 --> 26:55.875
Can we get another round?
Okay.

26:55.875 --> 26:57.354
And some more shots, please.
Sure!

26:57.354 --> 26:59.226
SARAH: No!
Oh, no, no, no! I--

26:59.226 --> 27:00.706
No.
No, no.

27:00.706 --> 27:03.099
Yeah, yeah.
MANDEL: We need to make a toast.

27:03.099 --> 27:04.144
Yes, yes, yes,
yes, yes.

27:04.144 --> 27:05.754
[ALL CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

27:05.754 --> 27:07.582
You guys, all right.

27:07.582 --> 27:10.541
A family that gets drunk
together, sleeps together.

27:10.541 --> 27:13.196
[LAUGHS]
Wait, wait, no.
That's-- Is that right?

27:13.196 --> 27:15.155
[LAUGHS]
This is coming out
of your mouth, no.

27:15.155 --> 27:17.026
SARAH:
Anyway.

27:17.026 --> 27:18.854
So, Denny,
what do you do for fun?

27:18.854 --> 27:19.986
Not much.

27:19.986 --> 27:21.204
Yeah, you don't have

27:21.204 --> 27:22.728
any hobbies or anything?

27:22.728 --> 27:26.035
Yeah, actually,
I collect comedy albums.

27:26.035 --> 27:27.428
That's unique.

27:27.428 --> 27:29.038
What got you into that?

27:29.038 --> 27:30.866
DENNY:
A couple years ago,
I went

27:30.866 --> 27:33.956
to one of those
record exchange stores.

27:33.956 --> 27:36.089
I was looking through
bins of music,

27:36.089 --> 27:39.005
and I came across
this album.

27:39.005 --> 27:41.660
And it was a compilation of all
these different
comedians.

27:41.660 --> 27:43.749
And something told me
to buy it, so I did.

27:43.749 --> 27:46.403
And whenever I was

27:46.403 --> 27:48.710
lonely or,
you know, feeling down,

27:48.710 --> 27:50.494
or just kinda
needed to laugh,

27:50.494 --> 27:54.324
I'd put it on, and it would
instantly make me feel better.

27:54.324 --> 27:55.717
Who's your
favorite comedian?

27:55.717 --> 27:58.241
Lenny Bruce.
