41:41.237 --> 41:45.111
A lie will be
people need no sleep at all.

41:45.111 --> 41:47.069
Truth is what is.

41:47.069 --> 41:49.028
If every politician,

41:49.028 --> 41:52.031
from the beginning,
is crooked,

41:52.031 --> 41:55.034
there is no crooked.
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

41:55.034 --> 41:57.166
[♪♪♪]

41:58.341 --> 42:01.954
♪ Your love ♪

42:01.954 --> 42:06.132
♪ Is gonna leave me
Yet again ♪

42:06.132 --> 42:10.049
♪ And, oh ♪

42:10.049 --> 42:14.793
♪ I thought I
was a friend ♪

42:17.622 --> 42:21.190
♪ Your love ♪

42:21.190 --> 42:25.630
♪ Is gonna kill me
Yet again ♪

42:25.630 --> 42:27.980
♪ And I'm bleeding out
For you ♪

42:27.980 --> 42:30.286
I brought you a jacket.
Thanks.

42:30.286 --> 42:31.679
[SNIFFLES]

42:34.682 --> 42:37.816
So...you can just
leave?

42:37.816 --> 42:41.950
He's gotta finish
processing my paperwork.

42:41.950 --> 42:45.911
♪ That nothing
Means more to me ♪

42:45.911 --> 42:49.392
♪ Than you and
I holding on ♪

42:49.392 --> 42:52.526
♪ To all that we can be ♪

42:52.526 --> 42:55.398
What do you wanna do?

42:55.398 --> 42:57.096
I was thinking we could
go to the park.

42:57.096 --> 42:58.619
Okay.

42:58.619 --> 43:00.534
♪ As I lay myself out
For you ♪

43:01.970 --> 43:05.278
♪ Anything ♪

43:05.278 --> 43:07.149
♪ As I lay myself ♪

43:07.149 --> 43:09.891
♪ All out for you ♪

43:09.891 --> 43:13.895
♪ Anything ♪

43:13.895 --> 43:16.898
♪ To see you
smile again ♪

43:16.898 --> 43:22.251
♪ I wanna see you
Smile again ♪

43:24.950 --> 43:26.560
♪ I wanna see you ♪

43:26.560 --> 43:28.170
So the rent's pretty cheap.

43:28.170 --> 43:29.258
♪ Smile again ♪

43:29.258 --> 43:30.956
I've never met
the landlord.

43:30.956 --> 43:34.089
So if something breaks,
I usually just fix it myself.

43:36.135 --> 43:38.616
Oh, yeah, it's...

43:38.616 --> 43:41.575
It's a lot.
I know.

43:41.575 --> 43:43.708
There's a lot of doubles
in there though.

43:43.708 --> 43:45.753
Usually, if I find one
in good condition,

43:45.753 --> 43:47.233
I just kind of buy it.

43:48.756 --> 43:50.540
What's this?

43:50.540 --> 43:52.412
Oh, that was there
when I moved in.

43:53.718 --> 43:55.458
Come on.

43:56.503 --> 43:58.331
Here's the bathroom.

44:00.550 --> 44:02.988
And, you know...

44:02.988 --> 44:04.859
the rest of the place.

44:04.859 --> 44:07.688
I know it's not a lot.
It's fine.

44:07.688 --> 44:10.038
I sleep on the couch,
so I made the bed up for you.

44:10.038 --> 44:11.649
Okay.
Come on,

44:11.649 --> 44:13.389
I'll show you
where it is.

44:24.662 --> 44:26.446
TV works.

44:26.446 --> 44:28.753
It gets three
channels,

44:28.753 --> 44:30.711
but it works.
Thanks.

44:32.104 --> 44:33.975
Do you want
something to drink?

44:33.975 --> 44:36.064
A glass of water.
Okay.

44:40.982 --> 44:44.464
So I've gotta work
a double tomorrow.

44:44.464 --> 44:47.249
Which means I'll probably
be gone before you get up,

44:47.249 --> 44:48.816
and I'll be getting home
pretty late.

44:48.816 --> 44:51.689
[WATER RUNS]

44:51.689 --> 44:54.213
I'll leave a key
and some money

44:54.213 --> 44:56.911
on the table
in the back room there.

44:56.911 --> 44:58.565
And if you want,

44:58.565 --> 45:01.960
I can bring you back some food
from the restaurant.

45:01.960 --> 45:03.657
You know, I'll probably--

45:03.657 --> 45:05.746
[♪♪♪]

45:05.746 --> 45:11.012
♪ And I'll do anything ♪

45:11.012 --> 45:14.363
♪ As I lay myself out
For you ♪

45:15.930 --> 45:18.977
♪ Anything ♪

45:18.977 --> 45:22.676
♪ As I lay myself
All out for you ♪

45:23.808 --> 45:26.854
♪ Anything ♪

45:26.854 --> 45:30.684
♪ To see you
smile again ♪

45:30.684 --> 45:36.429
♪ I wanna see you
Smile again ♪

45:38.997 --> 45:44.611
♪ I wanna
See you smile again ♪

45:47.266 --> 45:54.795
♪ Just to see you
Smile again ♪

45:54.795 --> 45:56.623
Hey, man,
welcome to Miller's.
Hi.

45:56.623 --> 45:58.538
You waiting
for your family, or...?

45:58.538 --> 46:01.889
Nope. It's just me.
Oh, okay.

46:01.889 --> 46:03.848
Hey...

46:03.848 --> 46:06.241
you're not Mandel's brother,
by chance?

46:06.241 --> 46:07.939
Why?
Because I'm black?

46:07.939 --> 46:09.984
No, it's 'cause
you're good-looking.

46:09.984 --> 46:12.378
Heh. It runs in the family.
Yeah, I'll bet.

46:12.378 --> 46:14.119
Hey, Nicholas.
Oh, hey, Sarah.

46:14.119 --> 46:16.774
I heard that you won
a race at your school.

46:16.774 --> 46:19.733
Yep!
Dang! That is awesome!

46:19.733 --> 46:23.128
All right, I'm gonna go
get your brother.
Okay.

46:23.128 --> 46:25.130
Do you want some sticky buns
or some pop while you wait?

46:25.130 --> 46:28.568
Can I get a water instead?
I'm in training.

46:28.568 --> 46:32.006
That is the cutest thing ever.
You got it. I'll be right back.

46:36.054 --> 46:39.187
So you're in training?
Yep, I'm pretty fast.

46:39.187 --> 46:40.885
You think
you're faster than me?

46:40.885 --> 46:42.712
Come on.

46:42.712 --> 46:45.019
I know, I'm a grown up,
and I may not look it,

46:45.019 --> 46:48.066
but I'm a pretty athletic guy.
In your dreams.

46:48.066 --> 46:50.720
You wanna find out?
Find out what?

46:50.720 --> 46:53.723
Who's faster.
You? Race me?

46:53.723 --> 46:56.291
That's what I'm saying.
You're crazy.

46:56.291 --> 46:57.945
Well?
Wait a minute.

47:00.339 --> 47:04.082
In here?
Out there.

47:05.083 --> 47:06.824
Oh, let me see.

47:08.608 --> 47:10.262
Okay, sure,

47:10.262 --> 47:12.699
but you're not
gonna win.

47:12.699 --> 47:13.961
DENNY:
How far is 40 meters?

47:13.961 --> 47:17.399
NICHOLAS:
Uh, no, no...

47:17.399 --> 47:19.749
Oh! To that pole!
DENNY: That pole right there.

47:19.749 --> 47:21.360
Yeah, that one.
MANDEL: Hey, Nick!

47:21.360 --> 47:24.363
Oh, hey, Mandel!
MANDEL: What's going on?

47:24.363 --> 47:27.888
About to find out who
the fastest man in Wisconsin is.

47:27.888 --> 47:30.151
Be careful, I don't want
anyone getting hurt.

47:30.151 --> 47:31.979
What the heck is everybody
doing outside?

47:31.979 --> 47:33.807
We got a restaurant to run
in here.

47:33.807 --> 47:35.417
Denny's racing
Nick.

47:35.417 --> 47:37.463
What? Hah!

47:37.463 --> 47:39.682
That's preposterous!
Heck, I could beat him.

47:39.682 --> 47:41.075
DENNY:
I just heard that.

47:41.075 --> 47:42.990
LLOYD:
Wanna put a little money
on that?

47:42.990 --> 47:44.949
DENNY:
I'll take that bet, Grandpa.

47:44.949 --> 47:47.255
LINDA:
What in God's name
is going on out here?

47:47.255 --> 47:50.824
SARAH:
Your husband and Denny are about
to have heart attacks.

47:50.824 --> 47:52.391
MANDEL: They're racing Nick.
Gonna race with that?

47:52.391 --> 47:54.088
LINDA:
What do you think you're doing,

47:54.088 --> 47:55.785
you're in no shape
to be playing around,

47:55.785 --> 47:58.136
You're going to hurt yourself.
LLOYD: Hush up, woman,

47:58.136 --> 48:00.486
I'm in the best shape
of my life. Don't say it.

48:00.486 --> 48:02.227
DENNY:
Mandel, would you do
the honors?

48:02.227 --> 48:03.358
MANDEL:
Sure.

48:06.013 --> 48:07.841
On your marks...
SARAH: Oh, I can't...

48:07.841 --> 48:09.495
Get set...

48:09.495 --> 48:11.845
What-what's the finish line?
Just run.

48:11.845 --> 48:14.065
Go!
What's the finish line?

48:14.065 --> 48:15.805
[ALL SHOUTING]
Run, grandpa, run!

48:15.805 --> 48:18.460
MANDEL: Go, Nick!
[CROWD LAUGHING]

48:18.460 --> 48:20.419
[ALL CHEERING]

48:20.419 --> 48:22.682
Oh, honey...

48:22.682 --> 48:24.989
DENNY: Aw, man.

48:24.989 --> 48:26.860
SHAUN:
That was awesome!

48:26.860 --> 48:28.775
SARAH: Good job!
MANDEL: Good job.

48:28.775 --> 48:33.345
LLOYD: No, I'm safe, I'm good.
[LAUGHTER]

48:33.345 --> 48:36.261
LLOYD:
All right, somebody, somebody,
somebody, somebody...

48:36.261 --> 48:37.915
LINDA:
Hey, good job.

48:39.046 --> 48:40.569
[SIGHS]

48:48.534 --> 48:50.014
[KNOB CLICKS]

48:51.711 --> 48:55.280
[MUSIC PLAYING FROM TV]

48:55.280 --> 48:58.718
MAN [ON TV]:
Chicago has a rhythm to it,
and a pulse to it,

48:58.718 --> 49:01.286
that you just don't find
in other places.

49:01.286 --> 49:03.157
Come, traveler,
and discover

49:03.157 --> 49:05.246
one of the world's
most fascinating cities.

49:05.246 --> 49:07.031
Chicago is something
you've just

49:07.031 --> 49:08.641
gotta experience
for yourself.

49:08.641 --> 49:11.905
Somebody needs to refill
the salt and pepper shakers!

49:11.905 --> 49:14.821
We know. Honey, please stop
driving us all nuts,

49:14.821 --> 49:19.086
just, you know, relax,
and keep that ice on your leg.

49:19.086 --> 49:21.871
Ow. Nobody told me
where the finish line was.

49:21.871 --> 49:23.438
How am I expected
to win the race

49:23.438 --> 49:25.179
if I don't know
where the finish line is?

49:25.179 --> 49:27.355
I want a rematch.
LINDA: That's not a good idea.

49:27.355 --> 49:29.575
Heh, heh!
I think it's a great idea.

49:31.490 --> 49:33.883
Kitchen's prepped
for tomorrow. We good?

49:33.883 --> 49:36.147
LLOYD:
Did we wipe down
the tables?

49:36.147 --> 49:38.366
SARAH: No, I'll do it, though.
DENNY: I can help.

49:38.366 --> 49:40.542
Yeah, I'll help you
and I'll lock up.

49:40.542 --> 49:41.587
SARAH: Okay.
Hm.

49:41.587 --> 49:44.894
Okay, follow me.

49:44.894 --> 49:48.028
LINDA:
Hey, guys, can you help me
get him in the car?

49:48.028 --> 49:49.638
LLOYD: I'm fine.
Okay.

49:49.638 --> 49:51.727
All right.
SHAUN: Come on, Grandpa.

49:51.727 --> 49:53.381
Don't call me Grandpa.
Hey.

49:53.381 --> 49:55.818
[LAUGHTER]
LLOYD: Ow-ow-ow! Boy. Oh, boy.

49:55.818 --> 49:57.646
LINDA:
Come on, big guy,
let's get you home.

49:57.646 --> 49:59.300
You need to heal up

49:59.300 --> 50:01.259
for the restaurant's
anniversary next week.

50:01.259 --> 50:04.044
LLOYD:
Yeah, that's not what you
want me healed up for, woman.

50:04.044 --> 50:05.872
MANDEL: Ooh, damn.
[LLOYD LAUGHS]

50:05.872 --> 50:08.135
LINDA:
Wow, fantasy thinking, baby...

50:11.617 --> 50:13.488
[♪♪♪]

50:50.612 --> 50:53.702
Would you care for
a late night snack?
Sure.

51:03.364 --> 51:05.279
Mm-mm.
These are good.

51:08.021 --> 51:10.502
That was really nice,
what you did earlier.

51:10.502 --> 51:12.504
Hm?
Letting Nicholas win.

51:12.504 --> 51:14.680
I was actually
trying to beat him.

51:14.680 --> 51:16.769
Sure you were.
Mm...

51:16.769 --> 51:19.424
It seems as if
the beautiful young lady's

51:19.424 --> 51:21.121
calling the nice young man
a fibber.

51:21.121 --> 51:24.081
[GASPS]
She most certainly is.

51:24.081 --> 51:25.734
I hope that
we can find some way

51:25.734 --> 51:28.650
for her to give him back
some trust.

51:28.650 --> 51:29.912
Why don't you just
come over here

51:29.912 --> 51:31.523
and give me a big
tomato smoochie.

51:31.523 --> 51:33.046
[SMOOCHES]
Smoochie?

51:33.046 --> 51:35.092
Maybe that's enough.

51:36.919 --> 51:39.183
Hey, can I show you something?
Of course.

51:46.059 --> 51:51.195
So...I been working
on some text for the new menu.

51:51.195 --> 51:52.979
I wanna know
what you think.

51:54.198 --> 51:56.722
Does Lloyd know
about this?

51:56.722 --> 52:00.073
No. I was gonna surprise him
at the anniversary.

52:00.073 --> 52:02.293
And I was hoping maybe
if it's good,

52:02.293 --> 52:04.121
he could use
a couple of the ideas.

52:07.080 --> 52:10.692
"At Miller's family restaurant,
you don't have to be related--"

52:10.692 --> 52:13.565
Could you just maybe
read it to yourself, please?

52:13.565 --> 52:15.001
Okay.
Thank you.

52:15.001 --> 52:16.829
I mean,
you're the artist.

52:16.829 --> 52:18.657
[♪♪♪]

52:23.966 --> 52:27.056
This is really nice.

52:27.056 --> 52:31.322
You think so?
Yeah, Lloyd is gonna love this.

52:31.322 --> 52:33.541
When I read the menu
for the first time--

52:33.541 --> 52:37.066
The fact that his grandmother
passed all those recipes down--

52:37.066 --> 52:40.026
The idea
of family traditions--

52:40.026 --> 52:42.028
I just,
I think it's really great.

52:42.028 --> 52:45.162
And what about your family?
Oh, my parents--

52:45.162 --> 52:47.555
They died a long time ago.
Oh...

52:47.555 --> 52:51.994
I'm sorry, I didn't know.
You mentioned a sister?

52:51.994 --> 52:54.171
Yeah. She's, um--

52:54.171 --> 52:56.695
Let's just say
we didn't really have

52:56.695 --> 52:59.524
the most traditional
family upbringing.

52:59.524 --> 53:02.091
Well, I mean,
who does?

53:02.091 --> 53:03.919
I mean, I've been raising
Isabella on my own

53:03.919 --> 53:09.055
from the very beginning,
and it's definitely challenging.

53:09.055 --> 53:11.405
But I mean,
like, she's the best thing

53:11.405 --> 53:13.494
that ever happened to me.

53:13.494 --> 53:16.367
I do wonder sometimes,
though,

53:16.367 --> 53:18.195
what my life
would have been like

53:18.195 --> 53:19.761
if I didn't have her
so young.

53:19.761 --> 53:22.721
I just, I think
I missed out on a lot.

53:22.721 --> 53:25.767
I kind of think I would've
been an amazing music teacher.

53:27.421 --> 53:31.730
Well, you probably are with her.
Awe, thank you.

53:31.730 --> 53:35.473
So what about her dad?

53:35.473 --> 53:38.476
Oh. Uh...
Heh, heh!

53:38.476 --> 53:41.218
That was a big mistake.
[SMACKS LIPS]

53:41.218 --> 53:43.263
Uh, he is way out
of the picture,

53:43.263 --> 53:44.699
which is a good thing.

53:44.699 --> 53:47.006
I mean, I think
that it's really important

53:47.006 --> 53:48.529
for children
to have a father,

53:48.529 --> 53:51.271
but it just didn't
work out that way.

53:51.271 --> 53:55.406
So then,
what about a boyfriend?

53:55.406 --> 53:59.410
I feel like she's a little young
to be dating, but...

53:59.410 --> 54:02.674
I meant you.
[CHUCKLES]

54:02.674 --> 54:04.502
Uh, no.

54:04.502 --> 54:07.766
I don't really have time
to date.

54:07.766 --> 54:10.159
Time is what I have.
Yeah?

54:10.159 --> 54:13.250
Yeah,
plenty of time.

54:13.250 --> 54:16.035
It's like I could probably
open up a clock shop.

54:16.035 --> 54:19.995
[CHUCKLES]
You know, you really are funny.

54:19.995 --> 54:21.867
You should incorporate
all of that,

54:21.867 --> 54:24.565
that whole bit, into your act
if you ever go on stage.

54:24.565 --> 54:27.133
There's actually--
There's this place in town

54:27.133 --> 54:29.353
that does
an open mic, so...

54:29.353 --> 54:33.008
Yeah, we'll see.
I'm just saying some--

54:33.008 --> 54:35.707
Some girls like a guy
that takes a chance.

54:39.624 --> 54:41.930
I'm gonna tell you
something,

54:41.930 --> 54:45.369
but you have to promise
not to say anything.

54:45.369 --> 54:47.327
All right.

54:47.327 --> 54:50.287
Pinky promise.
I promise.

54:50.287 --> 54:52.419
[♪♪♪]

54:54.291 --> 54:56.684
Okay.

54:56.684 --> 54:59.165
The story on the menu...

55:00.427 --> 55:02.037
It's fake.

55:02.037 --> 55:04.083
There's no
great grandmother

55:04.083 --> 55:06.651
with a traditional
family recipe.

55:06.651 --> 55:08.479
Lloyd comes from
a broken family,

55:08.479 --> 55:09.871
and for whatever reason,

55:09.871 --> 55:12.091
he stopped talking
to his family years ago.

55:12.091 --> 55:14.354
He met Linda
and they got married,

55:14.354 --> 55:16.400
but then she couldn't
have kids,

55:16.400 --> 55:17.662
so they opened
the restaurant

55:17.662 --> 55:19.141
and they've always
just kind of

55:19.141 --> 55:21.013
made their employees
feel like family,

55:21.013 --> 55:23.537
which is why I love it
so much.

55:23.537 --> 55:26.235
I don't know. I feel like
the story on the menu

55:26.235 --> 55:28.542
is probably something Lloyd
wished he had.

55:28.542 --> 55:30.414
You know, when you carry
a lie like that

55:30.414 --> 55:31.763
around with you long enough,

55:31.763 --> 55:34.113
you start to believe
it's the truth.

55:34.113 --> 55:36.724
But don't tell anyone
I told you.
No.

55:38.987 --> 55:41.860
I didn't mean to kill the mood.
No, it's fine.

55:41.860 --> 55:43.601
Give me a smile then.

55:46.908 --> 55:48.997
That's pathetic.

55:48.997 --> 55:52.566
Give me a better one or this is
going right in your face.

55:52.566 --> 55:54.133
Weak.

55:54.133 --> 55:56.396
Holy shit!
[DENNY LAUGHS]

55:56.396 --> 55:58.180
Oh man, those things
are sticky.

55:58.180 --> 56:02.271
Just don't.
This one's real sticky.

56:02.271 --> 56:04.317
[ENGINE HUMMING]

56:17.548 --> 56:19.898
♪ What to do with all my rage ♪

56:19.898 --> 56:23.205
♪ Since I quit systematically
Poisoning myself ♪

56:23.205 --> 56:24.772
Hi.
Hi.

56:24.772 --> 56:26.121
What can I get
for you?

56:26.121 --> 56:29.168
Um, I'm here
for the comedy night,

56:29.168 --> 56:32.519
to perform.
That's every Tuesday at nine.

56:32.519 --> 56:34.303
Hang on a second.

56:34.303 --> 56:36.654
♪ Let it all out
While you watch painfully ♪

56:36.654 --> 56:38.438
[MOUTHS]
Hey.

56:38.438 --> 56:40.832
♪ As I blend in
With all the urban crazies ♪

56:40.832 --> 56:43.051
Hi, I'm Becky.
I bartend.

56:43.051 --> 56:45.140
Denny.
[CHUCKLES]

56:45.140 --> 56:46.751
Go ahead and write your name
right here

56:46.751 --> 56:49.318
and please print
so it's legible.

56:50.972 --> 56:52.409
Looks like
you're going on at 11.

56:52.409 --> 56:53.671
Best to be early though,

56:53.671 --> 56:55.107
so we know
you're gonna perform.

56:55.107 --> 56:57.892
A lot of people
chicken out last minute.

56:57.892 --> 56:59.633
So what kind of comedy
do you do?

56:59.633 --> 57:02.810
Looks like we'll find out.
First time?

57:02.810 --> 57:05.857
Well, this is a great place
to get on stage and learn.

57:05.857 --> 57:07.946
Do you drink?
No, not really, no.

57:07.946 --> 57:10.078
Good. A lot of first timers
get drunk

57:10.078 --> 57:12.472
and they just make an ass
of themselves.

57:12.472 --> 57:14.474
Just get up there
and do your thing.

57:14.474 --> 57:18.173
Once you get the first laugh,
everything'll feel much easier.

57:18.173 --> 57:21.829
Wait for the laugh.
Always wait for the laugh.

57:21.829 --> 57:24.092
Mads, I'm home.

57:24.092 --> 57:26.138
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

57:32.449 --> 57:34.755
Hey, I brought some food
if you're hungry.

57:41.675 --> 57:43.068
Mads?

58:18.973 --> 58:20.671
[SIGHS]

58:24.065 --> 58:26.807
